of a symbolic terminal parse instance is 0;
\item
of an ethereal cause is 0;
\item
of the start EIM is 1;
\item
of a pair of matching causes
(top-down and bottom-up)
is the
maximum of the altitudes of the pair;
\item
of a cause set is
minimum of the altitudes of
the cause set's element;
\item
of an null-scan or prediction EIM is the altitude of
its cause set; and
\item
of an read or reduced EIM is one plus
the altitude of its cause set.
\end{itemize}
\end{definition}

